This paper deals with the problem of de-anonymizing social network users, which is a common topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and algorithm development, which are typical of the subfields of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of social network group memberships as a means of de-anonymization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of social network analysis (cs.SI) and data mining (cs.SD). Finally, the paper's focus on privacy and anonymity in social networks suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CY).
